<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Add VLC Playlist Submenus with Hidden or Fullscreen Star]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=595&amp;p=3036#p3036"><![CDATA[
VLC is made for Mac by a guy who really hates Windows and has done the least he could do to make it work with Windows.. and any issues related to windows often warrant a literal &quot;Screw Off&quot; from the developers, and endless anti-Windows rants... but if you dont mind tinkering around a bit, its a decent program for Command-line Switches... And the Full-screen Equalizer is hard to beat..<br /><br />If you have any other Media players you'd like to recommend that have comprehensive command-line options, and are more Windows-Minded &amp; Respectful of the Windows Platform, please post them here!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=359">Tenzen</a> — Sat Apr 27, 2013 4:18 am</p><hr />
